entry.title: Fix tablet mode controller requesting machine state too early
entry.content:
Tablet mode controller sends DBus request to powerd daemon for getting

the lid and detachable base status, then update the UI accordingly.

However, powerd may not be ready for the first time tablet controller

asking the status, thus the machine always stays in clamshell mode.



Update the tablet mode controller via overriding the

`PowerManagerBecameAvailable` member function, and perform requesting

switch status in it. With overriding this function, the first time

switch request is ensured to be sent after the powerd daemon is ready.



BUG=b:283533859

entry.title: Add DumpWithoutCrashing in TakeNavigationRequest
entry.content:
From the previous previous crash key we know the unexpected case that

the BFCached RenderFrameHost is destroyed without resetting the

associated NavigationRequest happens after the NavigationRequest is

created by before it's moved to the FrameTreeNode.



In this CL, the DumpWithoutCrashing from the destructor of the RFH

is removed, and a new DumpWithoutCrashing is added in

FrameTreeNode::TakeNavigationRequest.



A feature flag is added to ensure that the dump will only be taken

from dev/canary/beta.



Bug: 1474262, 1468984, 1470548
